---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service - plaite">
	<Header showBack />

	<section class="policy-page">
		<h1 class="section-title">Terms of Service</h1>
		<p class="section-subtitle">Please read these terms carefully before using the plaite app.</p>
		<p class="effective-date">Effective Date: July 17th, 2025</p>

		<div class="policy-content">
			<h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
			<p>By downloading, installing, or using the <strong>plaite</strong> mobile application ("App"), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service ("Terms"). If you do not agree to these Terms, do not use the App.</p>
		</div>

		<div class="policy-content">
			<h2>2. Description of Service</h2>
			<p>plaite is a meal planning application that helps users plan meals, create shopping lists, discover recipes, and manage their dietary preferences. The App may include features such as:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Meal planning and scheduling</li>
				<li>Recipe storage and sharing</li>
				<li>Shopping list generation</li>
				<li>Dietary preference management</li>
				<li>Nutritional information</li>
				<li>Social sharing features</li>
			</ul>
		</div>

		<div class="policy-content">
			<h2>3. User Accounts</h2>
			<h3>Account Creation</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>You must create an account to access certain features of the App</li>
				<li>You are responsible for maintaining the security of your account credentials</li>
				<li>You must provide accurate and complete information when creating your account</li>
				<li>You are responsible for all activities that occur under your account</li>
			</ul>
			<h3>Account Termination</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>You may delete your account at any time through the App settings</li>
				<li>We may suspend or terminate your account if you violate these Terms</li>
				<li>Upon termination, your access to the App will cease, and we may delete your account data</li>
			</ul>
		</div>

		<div class="policy-content">
			<h2>4. User Content</h2>
			<h3>Your Content</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>By using the App, you grant us a non-exclusive, royalty-free license to use, store, and display your User Content as necessary to provide the service</li>
				<li>You are responsible for ensuring you have the right to share any User Content you post</li>
			</ul>
			<h3>Prohibited Content</h3>
			<p>You may not post, upload, or share content that:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Is illegal, harmful, or violates any applicable laws</li>
				<li>Infringes on intellectual property rights</li>
				<li>Contains malicious code or harmful software</li>
				<li>Is spam, fraudulent, or misleading</li>
				<li>Violates the privacy or rights of others</li>
			</ul>
		</div>

		<div class="policy-content">
			<h2>5. Acceptable Use</h2>
			<p>You agree to use the App only for lawful purposes and in accordance with these Terms. You may not:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Use the App in any way that violates applicable laws or regulations</li>
				<li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to the App or its systems</li>
				<li>Interfere with or disrupt the App's functionality</li>
				<li>Use automated systems to access the App without permission</li>
				<li>Reverse engineer, decompile, or attempt to extract source code</li>
				<li>Use the App for commercial purposes without our written consent</li>
			</ul>
		</div>

		<div class="policy-content">
			<h2>6. Subscriptions and Payments</h2>
			<h3>Premium Features</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>Certain features may require a paid subscription</li>
				<li>Subscription fees are charged in advance and are non-refundable except as required by law</li>
				<li>Subscriptions automatically renew unless cancelled before the renewal date</li>
				<li>You can manage your subscription through your App Store account settings</li>
			</ul>
			<h3>Pricing Changes</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>We may change subscription prices with reasonable notice</li>
				<li>Price changes will not affect your current subscription period</li>
				<li>Continued use after price changes constitutes acceptance of new pricing</li>
			</ul>
		</div>

		<div class="policy-content">
			<h2>7. Intellectual Property</h2>
			<h3>Our Rights</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>The App and its content are protected by copyright, trademark, and other intellectual property laws</li>
				<li>We retain all rights to the App's design, functionality, and original content</li>
				<li>Our trademarks and logos may not be used without written permission</li>
			</ul>
			<h3>Third-Party Content</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>The App may include recipes, nutritional data, or other content from third parties</li>
				<li>Such content is the property of its respective owners</li>
				<li>We do not guarantee the accuracy of third-party content</li>
			</ul>
		</div>

		<div class="policy-content">
			<h2>8. Disclaimers</h2>
			<h3>Health and Nutrition</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>The App provides general meal planning and nutritional information for informational purposes only</li>
				<li>The App is not intended to provide medical advice or replace professional consultation</li>
				<li>Always consult healthcare professionals for medical advice regarding diet and nutrition</li>
				<li>We are not responsible for any health consequences resulting from use of the App</li>
			</ul>
			<h3>Service Availability</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>We strive to maintain App availability but cannot guarantee uninterrupted service</li>
				<li>The App may be temporarily unavailable for maintenance, updates, or technical issues</li>
				<li>We are not liable for any inconvenience caused by service interruptions</li>
			</ul>
		</div>

		<div class="policy-content">
			<h2>9. Limitation of Liability</h2>
			<p><strong>TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW:</strong></p>
			<ul>
				<li>WE ARE NOT LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, OR CONSEQUENTIAL DAMAGES</li>
				<li>OUR TOTAL LIABILITY SHALL NOT EXCEED THE AMOUNT YOU PAID FOR THE APP IN THE PAST 12 MONTHS</li>
				<li>WE ARE NOT LIABLE FOR ANY LOSS OF DATA, PROFITS, OR BUSINESS INTERRUPTION</li>
				<li>THESE LIMITATIONS APPLY EVEN IF WE HAVE BEEN ADVISED OF THE POSSIBILITY OF SUCH DAMAGES</li>
			</ul>
		</div>

		<div class="policy-content">
			<h2>10. Indemnification</h2>
			<p>You agree to indemnify and hold us harmless from any claims, damages, losses, or expenses arising from:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Your use of the App</li>
				<li>Your violation of these Terms</li>
				<li>Your User Content</li>
				<li>Your violation of any third-party rights</li>
			</ul>
		</div>

		<div class="policy-content">
			<h2>11. Privacy</h2>
			<p>Your privacy is important to us. Please review our <a href="/privacy-policy/">Privacy Policy</a> to understand how we collect, use, and protect your information.</p>
		</div>

		<div class="policy-content">
			<h2>12. Changes to Terms</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>We may update these Terms from time to time</li>
				<li>Continued use of the App after changes constitutes acceptance of the new Terms</li>
				<li>The current version will always be available at <a href="/terms-of-service/">plaite.io/terms-of-service</a></li>
			</ul>
		</div>

		<div class="policy-content">
			<h2>13. App Store Terms</h2>
			<p>Your use of the App is also subject to the terms and conditions of the applicable app store (Apple App Store, Google Play Store, etc.). In case of conflict between these Terms and app store terms, the app store terms shall prevail regarding your relationship with the app store.</p>
		</div>

		<div class="policy-content">
			<h2>14. Governing Law</h2>
			<p>These Terms are governed by the laws of <strong>Utah/USA</strong>, without regard to conflict of law principles. Any disputes will be resolved in the courts of Utah.</p>
		</div>

		<div class="policy-content">
			<h2>15. Severability</h2>
			<p>If any provision of these Terms is found to be unenforceable, the remaining provisions will continue in full force and effect.</p>
		</div>

		<div class="contact-info">
			<h3>Contact Information</h3>
			<p>If you have questions about these Terms, please contact us at:</p>
			<p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:dennis.dellacorte@plaite.io">dennis.dellacorte@plaite.io</a></p>
			<p><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://plaite.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://plaite.io</a></p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
	.policy-page {
		padding: 7rem 5% 3rem;
		max-width: 900px;
		margin: 0 auto;
	}

	.section-title {
		text-align: center;
		font-size: 2.8rem;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: var(--color-primary);
	}

	.section-subtitle {
		text-align: center;
		font-size: 1.15rem;
		color: var(--color-text-muted);
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
		max-width: 700px;
		margin-left: auto;
		margin-right: auto;
	}

	.effective-date {
		text-align: center;
		font-size: 1.05rem;
		color: var(--color-primary);
		font-weight: 600;
		margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
	}

	.policy-content {
		padding: 0.5rem 0;
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
	}

	.policy-content h2 {
		font-size: 1.8rem;
		margin: 2.5rem 0 1rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: var(--color-primary);
	}

	.policy-content h3 {
		font-size: 1.3rem;
		margin: 1.5rem 0 0.75rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: var(--color-text);
	}

	.policy-content p {
		margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
		color: var(--color-text);
		opacity: 0.9;
		font-size: 1.05rem;
		line-height: 1.7;
	}

	.policy-content a {
		color: var(--color-primary);
		font-weight: 600;
		transition: opacity 0.3s ease;
	}

	.policy-content a:hover {
		opacity: 0.8;
	}

	.policy-content ul {
		list-style: none;
		margin: 1rem 0;
		padding-left: 0.5rem;
	}

	.policy-content ul li {
		padding: 0.5rem 0;
		padding-left: 1.8rem;
		position: relative;
		color: var(--color-text);
		opacity: 0.9;
		font-size: 1.05rem;
		line-height: 1.6;
	}

	.policy-content ul li::before {
		content: '-';
		position: absolute;
		left: 0;
		color: var(--color-primary);
		font-weight: bold;
		font-size: 1.2rem;
	}

	.contact-info {
		background: var(--color-primary-light);
		padding: 2.5rem;
		border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
		margin-top: 3rem;
		text-align: center;
	}

	.contact-info h3 {
		font-size: 1.5rem;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
		color: var(--color-primary);
		font-weight: 700;
	}

	.contact-info p {
		margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
		font-size: 1.05rem;
	}

	.contact-info a {
		color: var(--color-primary);
		font-weight: 600;
		transition: opacity 0.3s ease;
	}

	.contact-info a:hover {
		opacity: 0.8;
	}

	@media (max-width: 768px) {
		.policy-page {
			padding: 5.5rem 4% 2rem;
		}
		.section-title {
			font-size: 2.2rem;
		}
		.policy-content h2 {
			font-size: 1.5rem;
		}
	}

	@media (max-width: 480px) {
		.policy-page {
			padding: 5rem 3% 1.5rem;
		}
		.section-title {
			font-size: 1.9rem;
		}
		.policy-content h2 {
			font-size: 1.4rem;
			padding-left: 1rem;
		}
		.policy-content p,
		.policy-content ul li {
			font-size: 0.95rem;
		}
		.contact-info {
			padding: 1.8rem 1.2rem;
		}
	}
</style>
